{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_antelope_ver01/data/ca06001655/00543171670/1920102901/0786.xml":{"full_text":"FOR\nTHOSE\nWHO\nTEACH\nHISTORY IN THE MAKING.\nFOR\nTHOSE\nWHO\nSTUDY\nHeadlines of the Week.\u2014October 20.\u2014Will Talk Over\nBritain\u2019s Strike; Negotiations Proceeding toward Settle\nment; Still After Draft Evaders in United States; King of\nGreece Reported Dead; Rumors of New Strikes Cause\nFear in England; Polish Troops Occupy Minsk Against\nOrders; Cox Will Ask Name of French Spokesman; Four\nArmy Planes Finish 9,000-Mile Flight. October 21.\u2014\nDeath of Greek King Denied; Cox Explains Article 10;\nEnglish Railway Men to Aid Coal Strikers; MacSwiney\nNow Fed by Force; Senator Reed Attacks Wilson and\nLeague; Armour in Profiteer Net; The \u201cDrys\u201d Keep after\nCox; Red Ultimatum to Armenia; Demand for Free Tran\nsit Refused; Howat\u2019s Ranks are Thin; Only the Radicals\nFollow Him; King Alexander Better; Harding Opens His\nNew York Campaign. October 22\u2014German\nminers\nEncourage British Strikers; Business Outlook Unusually\nBright, Says Gary, Steel Head; Shoe Prices Lower; Still\nNo Man\u2019s\nFeed MacSwiney; Reed Takes Stand in\nLand\u201d; Man Without Political Party; Tie-up May Force\nReturn to War Status in Britain; Colby to Reply to Root\nWet\u201d; Wheat\non Covenant; British Columbia Voted\nAgain Goes Over $2; Harding Returned to Marion;\nNominee Closes Campaign Except for a Few Ohio Speeches.\nOctober 23.\u2014Panic in Lithuania; \u201cIndependent\u201d Forces\nThreaten Kovno; President Will Make Another League\nAppeal; Will Speak to Delegation of Pro-League Repub\nlicans; Cox Again Enters New York; Campaign Expenses\nFiled in Congress; King Alexander\u2019s Condition Serious;\nCox Would Modify Taxation; Harding Would Foster\nIndustries; G. O. P. Says Inefficiency Adds Billions to\nNation\u2019s Debt; Reed\u2019s Friends Estranged by Recent\nSpeech; Famous Hotel in Geneva Taken Over as League\nCapital; Pendulum Swings Toward Peace in British\nMine Strike; \u201cHarding is Certain of Victory\u201d\u2014Hays;\nAssured of at Least 378 Electoral Votes, He Says. Octo\nber 24.\u2014To Investigate Chicago Board of Trade; President\nOrders Federal Trade Commission to Probe Charges of\nGrain Price Manipulation; Coolidge on Southern Trip;\nRussian Soviet Buys Machinery; Constantine May Grab\nThrone from Sick Son. October 25.\u2014Article 10 Not\nRegarded Vital, Says President of League Council; Mac\nSwiney Dead after 73 Days\u2019 Hunger Strike; New Out\nbreaks Feared in Ireland; Three British Guards Killed\nFollowing MacSwiney\u2019s Death; Cardinal Gibbons Favors\nLeague; Says Delay in Joining is Dangerous; Toyland is\nDisarming; Tin Soldiers and Cannons Not Popular This\nYear; Supreme Court Turns Down \u201cSuit to End War\u201d;\nOrient Railroad to Build into Mexico; Manitoba Will Vote\non Bone Dry Prohibition; Great Britain Sees Early End to\nStrike. October 26.\u2014King of Greece Dead; Throne to be\nOffered Paul, Third Son of Constantine; Harding Plans\nProtective Tariff; Wheat Took Jump; German Miners Will\nAttempt to Nationalize Mines; Nipped Sinn Fein Plot to\nAvenge MacSwiney; Japan Opposes Disarmament until\nAmerica Joins League; United States Inquires into Killing\nof More Americans in Mexico.\nNew Santa Fe Limited.\u2014The Santa Fe Railroad will\nput on a new limited train from Chicago to the Pacific\nCoast on November 14. When the roads were taken\nover by the Railroad Administration, the Santa Fe lost\nits position as a San Francisco line.\nThe new train re\nstores the line to its former status in this respect. Rail\nroad heads claim the public is getting better service and\nthat private administration of the roads is more economi\ncal than under Government supervision.\nLow Prices for Cotton.\u2014Cotton growers in the South\nare hard hit by the great drop in prices. Many plans are\nbeing considered for restoring a higher price, among them\na movement to plant but 50 per cent of the usual acreage\nnext year.\nIt is reported that many newspapers are\nbeing threatened with violence if they do not uphold\nthe demands for 50 cent cotton.\nAs the political campaign comes into its last days,\nsomething like the fervor of former ones is apparent.\nStill, the Literary Digest reports hundreds of the straw\nballots sent out are returned with inscriptions showing\nwidespread dissatisfaction with the tickets put up by the\ntwo leading parties. The league has finally become the\nonly issue that is attracting attention.\nBerea, the Mountain College.\u2014Attention was recently\ndirected to the Berea College, Kentucky, where the new\npresident, Willian James Hutchings, was installed. This\ncollege has for many years held out hope to the poor\nmountaineer desirous of obtaining a higher education,\nMore than 1,100 of the 1,560 students enrolled last year\ncame from the mountains of the South. All expenses\nfor a year may be met with $140, and a student may earn\nIt is needless to state, however, that not\na part of that.\nmany students have autos, or spend much time in society\nfunctions.\nGermany Buying Cows.\u2014Coincident with the demand\nof the allied powers for Germany to surrender a vast\nnumber of milk cows comes the news that Germany is\nbuying cows in the United States and will make a ship\nment of 30,000 from the port of Houston soon. Germany\nhad about 6 million cows at the opening of the war and at\nthe close had about 4 million. Two million of these had\nto be given up, according to Dr. Moeller, of Berlin, who is\nin this country making arrangements for shipping the cows\nto Germany.\nThe New Italy.\u2014In spite of the many reports of soviet\nseizure of factories and of general industrial unrest in\nItaly, it appears from recent information reaching us that\nItaly is up and doing. One thing that is contributing\nlargely to this regenerative movement is the presenceofso\nmany streams capable of producing electric energy.\nItalian engineers have achieved great things in the way of\npower generation and transmission, surpassing, it is said,\nthe work of American engineers along this line. Search in\nother directions has revealed that Italy has many un\ndeveloped resources. For instance, it is found that the\niron deposits are four times as great as was thought ten\nyears ago.\ndreamed-of quantities.\nAluminum and many other ores exist in un\nAltogether, Italy seems to be\nfinding herself industrially.\nGreat Spanish Exposition Planned.\u2014From Barcelona,\nSpain, comes the news that Catalonia, one of the ancient\nprovinces of that country, will undertake a world\u2019s ex\nposition in 1924. The exact title announced is the Inter\nnational Exposition of Electrical Industries and the\nGeneral Spanish Exposition. From this it will be seen\nthat electricity is to be emphasized in the exhibits. One of\nthe great features will be the Palace of Lights, where the\nlighting inventions and appliances made in all parts of the\nworld will be shown, Architects have completed the\nplans for the principal buildings and work has been begun\non some of them. The space covered by the exposition is\nabout 270 acres. An exclusively Spanish department will\nalso be a feature. In this the South American republics\nwill be prominently represented.","height":"17868","width":"12580"}}
